Since the total number of players is n = r + l, we have n = 3l.

The number of games won by left-handed players is 40% more than those won by right-handed players. Let x be the number of games won by right-handed players. Then left-handed players win 1.4x games.

Since all games are either won by left-handed or right-handed players, x + 1.4x = n(n-1)/2.

Substituting n = 3l, we get (3l)(2l) / 2 = 3l^2. So, 2.4x = 3l^2, hence x = 1.25l^2.

Therefore, the total number of games is 3l^2.

